Howell Police Athletic League

Howell Community Church
1554 Maxim Southard Road (at the corner of Victory Road)

Ardena Baptist Church
593 Adelphia Road (near Fairfield Road)

post_text: As we launch Week 2 of #HTPSRemoteLearning, we would like to extend a tremendous thank you to our whole community. Our staff and parents have partnered to make this endeavor truly about the children of Howell! There are way too many individuals to mention that have gone above and beyond, but please remember the members of our staff that are still working on-site in a limited capacity to ensure safe environments and seamless education. Thanks to our custodian, maintenance, grounds, transportation, food service and IT departments! #HTPSTalentTeams #HTPSLearnerSuccess #HowellLeads

As part of our COVID-19 readiness plan and as a precautionary measure, the Howell Township Public Schools will be operating on a shortened day/early dismissal schedule on Monday, March 16th. This will provide our staff to be best prepared in the event of a necessary closure due to the emerging information regarding COVID-19. Please know, we are not aware of any presumed positive or positive cases within our schools. Please check our website for the early dismissal schedule. The PAL After Care Programs will remain open.

Early Dismissal Schedule: https://www.howell.k12.nj.us/apps/pages/index.jsp?uREC_ID=1170562&type=d&pREC_ID=1420104

#HTPSCommunityEngagement #HTPSWellness #HTPSTalentTeams

post_text: There was a false social media post suggesting there is a confirmed case of COVID-19 at Middle School South. Please know that this is absolutely a false post and I have discussed this with Chief Kudrick, who has also confirmed that this is false. Again, there are no presumed positive or positive cases within our schools. Please know we will continue to update the situation surrounding this health concern as information becomes available. Be well.
